<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Leetcode on</title><link>https://kes.github.io/tags/leetcode/</link><description>Recent content in Leetcode on</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Sun, 07 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://kes.github.io/tags/leetcode/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Cyclical Thinking and the Zigzag Conversion Problem</title><link>https://kes.github.io/posts/cyclical-coding-fun/</link><pubDate>Sun, 07 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://kes.github.io/posts/cyclical-coding-fun/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;LeetCode has a well-known challenge, Zigzag Conversion (rated medium), introduced like this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Leetcode has a coding challenge &lt;a href="https://leetcode.com/problems/zigzag-conversion/description/"&gt;zigzag Conversion&lt;/a&gt; (rated at medium), that is presented like this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-text" data-lang="text"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;The string &amp;#34;PAYPALISHIRING&amp;#34; is written in a zigzag pattern on a given number of rows like this: (you may want to display this pattern in a fixed font for better legibility)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;P A H N
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;A P L S I I G
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Y I R
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;And then read line by line: &amp;#34;PAHNAPLSIIGYIR&amp;#34;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Interesting! How to solve it?&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Leetcode Algorithms 15</title><link>https://kes.github.io/leetcode/leetcode-algorithms-15/</link><pubDate>Fri, 29 Nov 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://kes.github.io/leetcode/leetcode-algorithms-15/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Okay, this is the fifteenth question from the &amp;ldquo;Top Interview 150.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
